Perfect spot being so close to the Jefferson park blue line. The inside is clean and classic diner looking with a few photos on the wall of the old jefferson park train stop. You order by the door (cash only) and then find yourself a seat and wait. I thought they would call my order but they bring it out to you and even filled my fountain drink for me (literally never had that done for me before), talk about service! I'm pretty sure it's family run, and that the family is the nicest family ever. Food was pretty good, classic diner dishes. I ordered the 3 eggs and corned beef hash. Came with the largest side of potatoes ever. I wish I got a little more hash and less potatoes, but besides that it was amazing. They do put a decent amount of butter on their toast so if that's not your thing, be sure to ask for no butter or butter on the side when you order.
